BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 730.60 Td (- First confirms that the FPGA enumerates in 25G mode.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 719.20 Td (- Then runs a basic camera pipeline before attempting multi-camera or AI demos.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 696.40 Td (For two physical cameras:) Tj ET
BT /F3 7.8 Tf 54 673.60 Td (python3 examples/agx5_multiviewer.py --cam 2 --lines 2160 --frame-rate 30 --receiver-type coe) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 652.60 Td (What this does / why required:) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 629.80 Td (- Runs the Group A 25G multiviewer with two real cameras.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 618.40 Td (- --receiver-type coe uses Thor's Camera-over-Ethernet path, which is the recommended 25G demo path.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 607.00 Td (- Use --cam 2 when only two physical cameras are installed. Do not use --cam 8 unless the demo scenario) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 595.60 Td (  requires replicated streams and the platform has been validated for it.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 572.80 Td (25G CoE Stability Workaround on AGX Thor) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 547.40 Td (For the 25G demo on AGX Thor, use CoE mode demos only. If running the demo repeatedly, refresh the MGBE) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 536.00 Td (  interface before every run after the first one:) Tj ET
BT /F3 7.8 Tf 54 513.20 Td (sudo ip link set mgbe0_0 down) Tj ET
BT /F3 7.8 Tf 54 503.60 Td (sudo ip link set mgbe0_0 up) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 482.60 Td (What this does / why required:) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 459.80 Td (- Briefly resets the Thor MGBE interface state between repeated 25G CoE demo runs.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 448.40 Td (- This avoids repeated-run stability issues observed on AGX Thor with 25G CoE demos.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 425.60 Td (Equivalent one-line command:) Tj ET
BT /F3 7.8 Tf 54 402.80 Td (sudo ip link set mgbe0_0 down ; sudo ip link set mgbe0_0 up) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 381.80 Td (This workaround was recommended for AGX Thor 25GbE demos to avoid issues seen on repeated CoE runs.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 359.00 Td (For debugging only, if CoE remains unstable, test with Linux receiver:) Tj ET
BT /F3 7.8 Tf 54 336.20 Td (python3 examples/agx5_multiviewer.py --cam 2 --lines 1080 --frame-rate 30 --receiver-type linux) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 315.20 Td (What this does / why required:) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 292.40 Td (- Forces the Linux socket receiver instead of CoE.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 281.00 Td (- This is useful as a diagnostic fallback, but CoE mode is the intended 25G demo path on Thor.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 258.20 Td (------------------------------------------------------------------------------) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 54 235.40 Td (8. MAX10 MIPI Power Fix) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 206.00 Td (Symptom) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 180.60 Td (Holoscan applications reached the FPGA/HSB, but camera configuration failed with I2C transaction errors:) Tj ET
BT /F3 7.8 Tf 54 157.80 Td (hololink._hololink.TransactionError: i2c_transaction i2c_address=0x37) Tj ET
BT /F3 7.8 Tf 54 148.20 Td (hololink._hololink.TransactionError: i2c_transaction i2c_address=0x1a) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 127.20 Td (Root Cause) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 101.80 Td (Early production MDK boards, both Group A and Group B, shipped with a bug in the MAX10 image. The buggy) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 90.40 Td (  MAX10 image does not apply power to the MIPI connectors. Without MIPI connector power, camera I2C) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 79.00 Td (  communication is impossible.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 498 28 Td (Page 6 of 9) Tj ET
