BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 742.00 Td (Customer release production boards are expected to ship with a fixed MAX10 image and should be plug-and-) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 730.60 Td (  play. Currently available early boards may need MAX10 reflashing.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 707.80 Td (Fix Applied) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 682.40 Td (1. Switch MAX10 onto the JTAG chain by setting SW4 on the carrier board to ON. This is the single switch) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 671.00 Td (  nearest the HDMI connector.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 659.60 Td (2. Use Quartus Programmer GUI to reflash MAX10 with:) Tj ET
BT /F3 7.8 Tf 54 636.80 Td (   max10_top_rtl_v1p1p6_fw_v2p0p1.pof) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 615.80 Td (3. Power off the board.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 604.40 Td (4. Set SW4 back to OFF so the FPGA appears on the JTAG chain again.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 581.60 Td (After this MAX10 update, camera I2C configuration succeeded.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 558.80 Td (Additional Note) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 533.40 Td (Initial production MDK batches may have a carrier micro USB hub that is susceptible to ESD. If the carrier) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 522.00 Td (  micro USB is not detected, for example Windows fails to read descriptors, use the standard JTAG connector) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.0 Tf 54 510.60 Td (  and a Byte Blaster.) Tj ET
